# Local-only learner data: contains emails, names, and activity events. The
# academy-visitor-sync scheduled task reads this file directly; the platform
# itself never serves it. Keep it on disk, never in git history.
visitors.json

# Gated content for the Internal track. Pushed to Cloudflare KV via
# internal-content/push.sh and served from the Worker, not from the repo.
internal-content/

# Local authoring tooling (academy-builder skill). Personal to the author,
# not part of the deployable platform.
skills/

# Authoring reference used by the academy-builder skill. Same category as
# skills/ above: local-only, not part of what the platform serves.
LESSON_AUTHORING_INSTRUCTIONS.md

# Reference copy of the prompt body for the academy-visitor-sync scheduled
# task. Internal operational workflow, not something the public repo needs.
academy-visitor-sync-updated-prompt.md
